cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.NA, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on efficient convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks on unstructured grids, specifically for spherical signals such as panorama images or planetary signals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of learnable parameters and back-propagation, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The use of differential operators and optimization methods may also suggest categories such as cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and reducing the number of network parameters may suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
